dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.cbe.loc.geo.address.UrbanPropertySubAddress
dataStructure.description:
An UrbanPropertySubAddress is used for addressing within a property in an urban area (country properties are often defined differently).. It may refer to a building, a building cluster, or a floor of a multistory building.This is an example of a concrete Geographic Location entity.

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: UrbanPropertySubAddress

child.name: levelType
child.description:
describes level types within a building

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: levelType

child.name: levelNr
child.description:
used where a level type may be repeated e.g. BASEMENT 1, BASEMENT 2

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: levelNr

child.name: buildingName
child.description:
allows for buildings that have well known names

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: buildingName

child.name: privateStreetName
child.description:
private streets internal to a property (e.g. a university) may have internal names that are not recorded by the land title office.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: privateStreetName

child.name: subUnitNr
child.description:
the discriminator used for the subunit often just a sumple number e.g. FLAT 5, may also be a range

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: subUnitNr

child.name: subUnitType
child.description:
the type of subunit e.g.BERTH, FLAT, PIER, SUITE, SHOP, TOWER, UNIT, WHARF

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: subUnitType
